Description: Handle sliver of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine pink-buff; cream slip. Circular stamp with rose symbol.
Curator's comments: Name Archokrates. Trimmed. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0090.01.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0737)
